CHAT.comment: Book Reading; The Very Hungry Caterpillar
Chi and Mot sit at kitchen table , hold book together. There is a dim light over the table. The tv is on in the background

Chi points to each word as he reads. Chi is a so-so reader. What sticks out are some of Mot's clues - they are semantic , with no relation to the story or to reading. Once , though , MOT points to picture for (ice cream) cone , and she sounds out most of the problem words in the post-food section (which goes very slowly). Mot helps when Chi pauses for a long time or asks what does this say.

u.a: stands up to see words better
another clue not to reading the word , but to what the word is
skips that night he had a stomachache
motions in a circle with her finger
